8 An Act relating to motor vehicles; creating the
Shelby Johnson and Logan Deardorff Act of 2025;
9 amending 47 O.S. 2021, Section 6-207, as amended by
Section 70, Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp.
10 2023, Section 6-207), which relates to authority to
deny application for or cancel license for certain
11 ailments; deleting certain reporting requirement;
requiring certain diagnosis report; stating certain
12 report shall not be considered public record;
authorizing the promulgation of certain rules;
13 providing for noncodification; and providing an
effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Shelby Johnson
20 and Logan Deardorff Act of 2025".
21 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 6-207, as
22 amended by Section 70, Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2024,
23 Section 6-207), is amended to read as follows:
